INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4900','letter','1777-01-11','Paris','','FRA','John','Laurens','','James','Laurens','','individual','','Lord Stormont discovered that these vessels were employed by Silas Deane, and the cargoes intended for America. He went immediately, at an unusual hour for business, to Versailles','ltr_jol4900.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4901','letter','1777-08-13','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The men are exercised in smaller or greater numbers every day. The country people bring in a plenty of vegetables, &c. and we hear very few complaints from those immediately about us of the violations of private property.','ltr_jol4901.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4902','letter','1777-08-21','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','If the enemy have a design upon Charles Town which does not so clearly appear to me as it does to most people, I hope we shall ruin the northern branch of their army','ltr_jol4902.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4903','letter','1777-08-26','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Messrs. Pinckney and Horry arriv\'d here yesterday, but they could not inform me certainly whether you had employ\'d Hunt to buy me a horse.','ltr_jol4903.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4904','letter','1777-09-26','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','We shall move towards Philadelphia to-day, as the weather is fair and our reinforcements are at some distance below, ready to fall in with us.','ltr_jol4904.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4905','letter','1777-10-15','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I beg leave to felicitate you upon the victory gained over the haughty Burgoyne, a victory which derives much of its importance from the critical time in which it happened.','ltr_jol4905.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4906','letter','1777-11-06','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','This days Philadelphia paper contains Gen Burgoyne\'s Letter to s\'r W\'m Howe : as I cannot send you the paper itself I copy the letter','ltr_jol4906.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4907','letter','1777-11-07','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','There have been several women from Ph a within two days past, who have applied for leave to pass into the country declaring that unless this indulgence be granted to them, they must inevitably starve.','ltr_jol4907.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4908','letter','1777-11-09','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Craig of Moylan\'s Light Dragoons, with sixteen horsemen surprised one of the enemy\'s patrols this morning, consisting of seven horse and seven grenadiers and took the whole party prisoners','ltr_jol4908.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4909','letter','1777-11-14','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','A considerable breach was made on the 11th in the masonry of the fort, many palisades were level\'d, the block houses almost ruin\'d, several cannon dismounted, and a valuable artillery officer kill\'d.','ltr_jol4909.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4910','letter','1777-11-18','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','You, my dear father will call me a presumptuous young man, especially when you hear that three general officers are gone to investigate these points on the spot.','ltr_jol4910.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4911','letter','1777-11-26','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Your kind letter of the 23d announces a very accept able reinforcement of linnen for which I am exceedingly obliged to you the boots will come in good time those which I wear at present are in good condition','ltr_jol4911.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4912','letter','1777-11-29','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Gen\'l Greene has joined us, and our forces are reunited. The enemy after razing Bilingsport and Red Bank have quitted the Jerseys altogether.','ltr_jol4912.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4913','letter','1777-12-03','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','We have received several accounts from outposts within a few days past intimating that an attack upon us was meditated. We have in consequence prepared ourselves','ltr_jol4913.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4914','letter','1777-12-15','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The army cross\'d the Schuylkil on the 13th and has remained encamped on the heights on this side. Our truly republican general has declared to his officers that he will set the example of passing the winter in a hut himself','ltr_jol4914.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4915','letter','1777-12-23','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The matter was in brief as follows : when we march\'d from Whitemarah Camp, and were in the act of crossing the Schuylkil, we received intelligence that the enemy were advancing on this side of the river','ltr_jol4915.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4916','letter','1778-01-01','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The soldiers are nearly covered with good huts. The North Carolinians are the most backward in their buildings, and for want of sufficient energy to exert themselves once for all, will be exposed to lasting evils.','ltr_jol4916.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4917','letter','1778-01-03','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','By this day\'s courier, you will be informed of a base insult offer\'d to the Commander in chief, which will raise your indignation.','ltr_jol4917.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4918','letter','1778-01-05','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Some commercial technicalities puzzled me in the letters which you sent me to translate. My French acquaintance here are almost as much at a loss','ltr_jol4918.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4919','letter','1778-01-14','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','This will be delivered to you by the Chevalier de Mauduit de Plessis, whose name I mentioned to you in one of my late letters. I am happy in having an opportunity of recommending so worthy a man to your protection.','ltr_jol4919.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4920','letter','1778-01-17','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','first, I would advance those who are unjustly deprived of the rights of mankind to a state which would be a proper gradation between abject slavery and perfect liberty, and besides I would reinforce the defenders of liberty with a number of gallant soldiers.','ltr_jol4920.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4921','letter','1778-01-23','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The resolution of Congress respecting Gen\'l Burgoyne and his army, I think both founded in justice and policy. It might have been better perhaps if a little more republican laconism had been used in explaining the reasons for it.','ltr_jol4921.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4922','letter','1778-01-28','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The intended expedition to Canada that gentleman had communicated to me the day before in confidence, and by giving me the perusal of his letter to you on the subject had discovered his aversion to a certain general as second in command.','ltr_jol4922.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4923','letter','1778-02-02','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','You seem to think, my dear father, that men reconciled by long habit to the miseries of their condition, would prefer their ignominious bonds to the untasted sweets of liberty, especially when offer\'d upon the terms which I propose.','ltr_jol4923.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4924','letter','1778-02-03','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I am happy in having an opportunity of introducing to your acquaintance the brave Col Fleury, whose reputation is not unknown to you.','ltr_jol4924.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4925','letter','1778-02-03','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I am happy in having the pleasure of introducing to your acquaintance, Colonel Fitzgerald, the senior aid in our family.','ltr_jol4925.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4926','letter','1778-02-09','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I have to thank you, my dear father, for two shirts, and a piece of scarlet cloth. I wrote to James for some hair powder and pomatum, but received only the latter with a comb.','ltr_jol4926.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4927','letter','1778-02-08','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I forgot to inform you of an interesting letter which the general received this morning from Sir Wm. Howe, in which he declares that he is ready to give his consent to a General exchange of prisoners upon the terms formerly offered by Gen\'l Washington','ltr_jol4927.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4928','letter','1778-02-15','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The presumption which would lead me to pursue my project after what you have said upon it, would be unpardonable ; praying your forgiveness therefor, my dear friend, for the trouble which I have given you on this eccentric scheme','ltr_jol4928.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4929','letter','1778-02-17','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','We have lately been in a most alarming situation for want of provisions. The soldiers were scarcely restrained from mutiny by the eloquence and management of our officers.','ltr_jol4929.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4930','letter','1778-02-24','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I deplore the misfortune of Charlestown if it has fallen upon individuals of moderate fortune ; if it affects only a number of rich men, it will contribute to equalizing estates, I shall not regret it.','ltr_jol4930.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4931','letter','1778-02-24','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I have but one pair of breeches that are wearable.','ltr_jol4931.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4932','letter','1778-02-28','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I was obliged to write briefly and in haste, by the last courier. I have since had several long conversations with the Baron Steuben, who appears to me a man profound in the science of war, and well disposed to render his best services to the United States.','ltr_jol4932.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4933','letter','1778-03-09','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The method which you allude to, of procuring the necessary article in question, has been clandestinely practiced by many.','ltr_jol4933.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4934','letter','1778-03-14','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The dislike of some of his officers to him as a stranger, the advantages which they have taken of him as such, and their constant contrivances to thwart him on every occasion, made it impossible for him to command','ltr_jol4934.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4935','letter','1778-03-22','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','This will be delivered to you by Brigadier General Du Portail, commanding officer of Engineers, whom I am glad of having an opportunity of introducing to your acquaintance.','ltr_jol4935.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4936','letter','1778-03-25','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I am grieved that you persevere in your resolution of retiring from Congress. Your reelection is a testimony of the good opinion of your countrymen','ltr_jol4936.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4937','letter','1778-03-28','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','we had some serious conversation together upon the subject of your retiring from Congress, in which we determined that your presence in that assembly is more necessary now, than it would have been at any other period since the revolution.','ltr_jol4937.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4938','letter','1778-04-01','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Our commissioners proceeded yesterday morning to German Town according to agreement, and a strict neutrality and suspension of hostilities are to be observed in all the extent of the village during the conference.','ltr_jol4938.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4939','letter','1778-04-05','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The conduct of Congress in giving orders to officers on detached commands, without communicating them to the General, is not only a deficiency of politeness, considered as an omission of a compliment which is due to him, but likewise a breach of military propriety.','ltr_jol4939.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4940','letter','1778-04-11','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I must confess to you, with grief, my dearest friend, that upon a nearer view, I have a far less respectable idea of my countrymen than when I beheld their struggle from afar, and could not distinguish the vices with which they are oppressed.','ltr_jol4940.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4941','letter','1778-04-18','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The General sends you a handbill which has been artfully thrown out by the enemy, and which, unless properly counteracted, will undubitably tend to foment disunion, perhaps the only and evidently the surest method of destroying us.','ltr_jol4941.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4942','letter','1778-04-20','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','You will receive by this courier, L\'d North\'s recantation. It would make an admirable contrast with a vehement oration which I heard him pronounce in the confidence of success, while I was in England.','ltr_jol4942.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4943','letter','1778-04-27','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The pardons offered to the subjects of the states who had embraced the party of the enemy, will, I am persuaded, be attended with extensive good consequences.','ltr_jol4943.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4944','letter','1778-04-01','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I snatch a minute to congratulate my dear father, upon the important intelligence from France. As the matter is represented she seems to have acted with politic generosity towards us','ltr_jol4944.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4945','letter','1778-04-04','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I thank you my dear father for your kind favour of yesterday, and again congratulate you upon the important intelligence from France.','ltr_jol4945.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4946','letter','1778-04-07','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Yesterday we celebrated the new alliance, with as much splendour as the short notice would allow. Divine service preceded the rejoicing.','ltr_jol4946.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4947','letter','1778-05-12','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I felicitate you upon the declaration of war between England and France ; for though we have no positive intelligence of the event, its immediate and sure precursors have taken place','ltr_jol4947.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4948','letter','1778-04-21','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The Marquis made a brilliant retreat, and left the surrounding enemy to return to the city with precipitation.','ltr_jol4948.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4949','letter','1778-06-09','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Some people are of opinion that the arrival of the commissioners at Philadelphia is a proof that war is not yet declared between England and France','ltr_jol4949.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4950','letter','1778-06-09','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The insolence and infatuation of the British minister in sending commissioners to treat with America, under the act of Parliament which he pretends to call conciliatory, are without parallel.','ltr_jol4950.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4951','letter','1778-06-11','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The commissioners ventured out yesterday as far as German Town with an escort of light troops, which with the number that have crossed into the Jerseys, left only 800 men in the city according to the account of a very intelligent deserter.','ltr_jol4951.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4952','letter','1778-06-14','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The inquiry into the conduct of the late quarter masters, must give pleasure to every man who wishes to see the betrayers of public trusts brought to condign punishment.','ltr_jol4952.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4953','letter','1778-06-15','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The world looks with anxious expectation for the answer of Congress to the British commissioners. A paper was said to have been pasted up in camp, which contained the terms that are offered on their part.','ltr_jol4953.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4954','letter','1778-06-16','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The state of intelligence yesterday was as follows : That the baggage of the commissioners was packed up, their linnen ordered from the washerwomen finished or unfinished','ltr_jol4954.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4955','letter','1778-06-30','English Town','STATE','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The delay, however, will be attended with this advantage, that I shall be better able to give you an account of the enemy\'s loss ; tho I must now content myself with a very succinct relation of this affair.','ltr_jol4955.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4956','letter','1778-07-02','New Brunswick','STATE','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I have since had of the enemy\'s strength and designs, it is evident to me that Mr Clinton\'s whole flying army would have fallen into our hands, but for a defect of abilities or good will in the commanding officer of our advanced corps.','ltr_jol4956.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4957','letter','1778-07-06','New Brunswick','STATE','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I beg leave to introduce to your acquaintance, and recommend to your civilities the Marquis de la Yienne. He arrived in camp while we were at Valley Forge, with recommendatory letters to the Marquis De Lafayette','ltr_jol4957.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4958','letter','1778-07-07','New Brunswick','STATE','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','We are just about to march. Seventy miles are between us and King\'s Ferry, where we shall probably cross the North river.','ltr_jol4958.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4959','letter','1778-07-13','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','my heart overflows with gratitude at the repeated proofs of your tender love ; and must defer answering your kind letters of the 6th and 10th , till my return from Count D\'Estaing\'s fleet','ltr_jol4959.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4960','letter','1778-07-18','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','I am very happy in having an opportunity of introducing to your acquaintance, General Forman, a gentleman for whom I have the highest esteem','ltr_jol4960.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4961','letter','1778-07-18','Black Point','STATE','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Upon my arrival here with dispatches from the General to Admiral D\'Estaing, I found that the fleet laboured under the greatest difficulty in procuring water','ltr_jol4961.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4962','letter','1778-07-22','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Permit me to introduce to your acquaintance the Baron D Arendt, Col. of the German batallion, who in consequence of disputes with his corps of officers, which he thinks make it inconvenient with his honour to serve with them again','ltr_jol4962.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4963','letter','1778-08-04','Providence','STATE','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','Upon my delivering Gen\'l Washington\'s dispatches, and Gen\'l Sullivan\'s containing a plan of operations, the Admiral informed me his intention had been to proceed immediately into the main channel of Newport and attack the enemy\'s batteries.','ltr_jol4963.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4964','letter','1778-08-22','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','According to the first plan proposed by General Sullivan, the American forces were to land on the east side of Rhode Island under cover of the fire of three frigates stationed in the eastern channel for that purpose.','ltr_jol4964.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4965','letter','1778-09-15','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The intelligence which we have received since my last, confirms the idea of a grand move on the part of the enemy.','ltr_jol4965.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4966','letter','1778-09-24','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The information which you give me relative to my hospitable acquaintance, gives me great pain. I had conceived an esteem for him, and it afflicts me to find a new instance of the depravity of my species.','ltr_jol4966.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4967','letter','1778-10-07','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The M. de Lafayette will not long have delayed after his arrival to open to you a plan for introducing French troops into Canada.','ltr_jol4967.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jol4968','letter','1778-10-13','','','US','John','Laurens','','Henry','Laurens','','individual','','The late bad weather drove that detachment of the enemy, that was posted on Valentine\'s hill, into the city, and they now confine themselves within Kingsbridge.','ltr_jol4968.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Army Correspondence of Colonel John Laurens in the Years 1777 - 78');
